Public Domain, from the British Library's collections, 2013

The Siege of Londonderry in 1689, as set forth in the literary remains of Col. the Rev. G. Walker, D.D., which are now first collected and comprise 1. A True Account of the Siege. 2. A Vindication of the True Account. 3. A Letter on the Treachery of Lundy. 4. Other official letters. 5. Sermons, prayers and speeches during the Siege. With notes original and selected ... and numerous illustrations. Edited by the Rev. P. Dwyer
